title: Should we nullify previous vote
body:
The previous vote selected OPS Proposal 2.

During the community call, sentiment was that we would vote for "Neither" option.  However; the results of the snapshot vote selected one of the proposals. The core team has asked to nullify the previous vote and requested that I removed my grant proposal. Thank you for the votes and support. In support for the community, if the previous vote is nullified I will remove my grant request from the ops distribution and make a separate proposal. Also, based on review of the SourceCred initiatives, core team will audit and adjusted initiatives before the next ops distribution vote.

The current proposal seeks to nullify the previous SNAPSHOT proposal  https://snapshot.org/#/metafactory.eth/proposal/QmczN7Chj7mAwznVrqachMcm3TKZjBk2htqtF9ZJFrcgXN

Vote For Nullification: Previous vote will be nullified and OPS distribution will return to the discussion phase for further refinement.  

Vote Against Nullification: Previous vote should be considered accurate. OPS distribution should commence, penguin will not make a separate grant proposal.

Vote Abstain: Do not vote for either outcome, delegate response to community decision.
